---
source: tests/cli.rs
expression: help
---
Transfer Venmo balance to the unique selected standard bank destination

Usage: out [OPTIONS] <AMOUNT_OR_ALL>

Arguments:
  <AMOUNT_OR_ALL>
          Positive USD amount, or `all` to use the fresh available-balance snapshot

Options:
      --speed <SPEED>
          Transfer speed; defaults to standard, the only currently accepted value

          [default: standard]
          [possible values: standard]

      --yes
          Skip only the final default-No confirmation

      --dry-run
          Complete preflight and show details without creating the transfer

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

Confirmation defaults to No. Exact lowercase `all` resolves once from a fresh available-balance snapshot, excludes on-hold funds, and is not an atomic account drain. Financial exit code 3 means the transfer outcome must be verified independently. Do not retry; check `activity list` and the official Venmo app. This subcommand supports only standard bank cash-out; instant, debit, manual destination selection, and challenge continuation remain unavailable.
